## Scott Brick as Dune Narrator

Scott Brick has been narrating Dune audiobooks for over 20 years, working on the ground floor of Arrakis-related content. He narrated Herbert's original Dune novel back in the early 2000s, along with dozens of other Dune stories by Frank Herbert, Brian Herbert and Kevin J. Anderson. He estimates having narrated at least 25 Dune books, possibly 26.

## Dune Audiobook Details

The Dune audiobook features multiple narrators including Scott Brick, Orlagh Cassidy, Euan Morton, Simon Vance, Ilyana Kadushin, Byron Jennings, David R. Gordon, Jason Culp, Kent Broadhurst, Oliver Wyman, Patricia Kilgarriff, and Scott Sowers. This full-cast performance is augmented by sound effects and music, with Simon Vance serving as the stalwart anchor narrator and Scott Brick contributing to the engrossing presentation.

Scott Brick delivers a masterful performance of this science fiction classic, and he narrates like a historian of the planet Dune, expressing a passion for the peoples and cultures he describes.
